WEBVTT

00:00:11.011 --> 00:00:15.015
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

00:00:17.767 --> 00:00:18.893
I knew they'd do it.

00:00:21.312 --> 00:00:22.814
- Hello, sir. - Yeah.

00:00:25.400 --> 00:00:29.738
YEONSEO UNIVERSITY PROGRAMMING COMPETITION RESULTS

00:00:34.117 --> 00:00:36.077
KIM SE-YUN, LEE KANG

00:00:36.661 --> 00:00:39.122
RUNNER-UP

00:00:42.375 --> 00:00:43.376
Mr. Heo.

00:00:43.960 --> 00:00:44.960
Jesus Christ!

00:00:44.961 --> 00:00:46.838
It's just me. Why are you so surprised?

00:00:48.548 --> 00:00:51.426
I was going to tell you, but you've already seen.

00:00:55.138 --> 00:00:56.139
Hey.

00:00:56.931 --> 00:00:59.099
Why are you runner-up? You knew the problems.

00:00:59.100 --> 00:01:03.354
I threw a few of the problems. If we won, we'd be going to the finals.

00:01:04.272 --> 00:01:05.607
That wouldn't be fair.

00:01:09.152 --> 00:01:10.195
I'm going

00:01:10.695 --> 00:01:12.238
To Se-yun's house tomorrow.

00:01:12.739 --> 00:01:14.240
To have dinner with them.

00:01:15.200 --> 00:01:16.201
I was invited.

00:01:18.411 --> 00:01:19.245
I see.

00:01:20.038 --> 00:01:22.540
Then our lessons will start this weekend.

00:01:23.750 --> 00:01:25.793
Submit your assignment by email before then.

00:01:25.794 --> 00:01:26.795
Okay.

00:01:27.295 --> 00:01:28.463
See you Saturday, then.

00:01:30.381 --> 00:01:31.382
Hey, Lee Kang.

00:01:38.431 --> 00:01:40.516
You do know this has to be our secret?

00:01:40.517 --> 00:01:42.309
It stays between us.

00:01:42.310 --> 00:01:43.478
I know.

00:02:01.287 --> 00:02:02.914
- Hello, sir. - Yeah, hi!

00:02:04.541 --> 00:02:06.667
The act of writing itself helps you think...

00:02:06.668 --> 00:02:08.794
...no complete blueprint in your mind.

00:02:08.795 --> 00:02:11.214
It's akin to going on a journey without a map.

00:02:13.550 --> 00:02:15.134
Yes, well...

00:02:15.135 --> 00:02:17.720
<i>If I push a large door open and enter,</i>

00:02:18.388 --> 00:02:20.306
<i>only to find another smaller door,</i>

00:02:20.890 --> 00:02:22.851
<i>did I ever really step inside,</i>

00:02:23.560 --> 00:02:25.311
<i>or was I outside all along?</i>

00:02:29.107 --> 00:02:30.275
A smaller door?

00:02:46.374 --> 00:02:47.208
How thoughtful.

00:02:48.626 --> 00:02:51.004
How did you know that Yun's mom likes white roses?

00:02:51.671 --> 00:02:54.674
Yun told me, actually.

00:02:56.926 --> 00:02:58.678
But I could only afford three.

00:03:00.263 --> 00:03:02.306
How's the food? Do you like it?

00:03:02.307 --> 00:03:05.392
Yes, it's delicious. I'm enjoying all of it.

00:03:05.393 --> 00:03:07.061
Thank you for inviting me.

00:03:07.562 --> 00:03:10.772
Not at all. We should be the ones thanking you.

00:03:10.773 --> 00:03:13.317
Thanks to you, Kang, our Yun won an award.

00:03:13.318 --> 00:03:14.569
Runner-up, no less.

00:03:15.069 --> 00:03:17.363
We never expected that much.

00:03:17.864 --> 00:03:20.825
Please take good care of our Yun.

00:03:22.702 --> 00:03:24.662
Kang, do you have any siblings?

00:03:25.413 --> 00:03:26.247
Sorry?

00:03:29.167 --> 00:03:30.376
Oh, siblings?

00:03:31.085 --> 00:03:32.085
It's just me.

00:03:32.086 --> 00:03:33.630
So you're an only child.

00:03:34.130 --> 00:03:37.050
Where do your parents live? What do they do?

00:03:40.303 --> 00:03:42.931
<i>A mother bird's anxious efforts to protect her young.</i>

00:03:44.807 --> 00:03:46.476
<i>The second door I encountered.</i>

00:03:46.976 --> 00:03:49.229
Goodness, honey.

00:03:49.896 --> 00:03:51.522
Why would you ask him that?

00:03:52.815 --> 00:03:53.941
I just...

00:03:53.942 --> 00:03:57.027
Wait, was that rude of me? Is it not okay to ask?

00:03:57.028 --> 00:04:00.323
Kang doesn't talk about himself much. He doesn't like to.

00:04:00.823 --> 00:04:01.658
Is that so?

00:04:02.158 --> 00:04:05.911
I see. Then I guess that <i>was</i> rude of me.

00:04:05.912 --> 00:04:06.829
I'm sorry.

00:04:07.705 --> 00:04:08.873
My apologies.

00:04:09.749 --> 00:04:12.251
If we're all done eating, should we have dessert?

00:04:12.252 --> 00:04:13.836
- Yeah. - Fruit? Or cake?

00:04:14.921 --> 00:04:16.047
I don't have a mom.

00:04:20.969 --> 00:04:22.345
<i>I needed a key.</i>

00:04:22.887 --> 00:04:25.138
<i>A key that could unlock that door.</i>

00:04:25.139 --> 00:04:27.600
She left us when I was eight.

00:04:31.187 --> 00:04:34.440
My dad got hurt doing construction work and was sick for a long time.

00:04:35.817 --> 00:04:38.653
He's in a nursing home now due to alcohol-induced dementia.

00:04:42.323 --> 00:04:43.241
Then...

00:04:44.951 --> 00:04:46.577
Who did you live with?

00:04:47.078 --> 00:04:48.788
- Honey. - It's all right.

00:04:50.581 --> 00:04:51.666
I understand your curiosity.

00:04:54.043 --> 00:04:56.795
Yes, I'm asking because I'm genuinely worried.

00:04:56.796 --> 00:04:58.839
I wonder who took care of him.

00:04:58.840 --> 00:05:00.800
Any parental figures.

00:05:01.759 --> 00:05:02.593
I did.

00:05:05.388 --> 00:05:06.639
I took care of myself

00:05:07.932 --> 00:05:09.017
And my dad.

00:05:12.312 --> 00:05:14.938
It was just us two until he was hospitalized.

00:05:14.939 --> 00:05:18.318
From second grade until I started university.

00:05:19.569 --> 00:05:21.070
Goodness.

00:05:21.571 --> 00:05:22.613
So,

00:05:23.656 --> 00:05:25.992
You studied while taking care of your dad

00:05:26.492 --> 00:05:28.119
And still got into Yeonseo?

00:05:28.786 --> 00:05:31.497
Kang's grades even got him a full scholarship.

00:05:32.165 --> 00:05:33.165
Right?

00:05:33.166 --> 00:05:34.876
I worked really hard.

00:05:36.627 --> 00:05:38.588
I didn't want people to know my situation.

00:05:40.048 --> 00:05:42.424
Nor did I want to be a burden to anyone.

00:05:42.425 --> 00:05:46.220
So I studied like crazy between my part-time jobs.

00:05:48.639 --> 00:05:50.850
But I don't feel alone anymore.

00:05:53.978 --> 00:05:55.521
Because I made a friend.

00:05:57.148 --> 00:05:59.192
Someone who's completely different from me.

00:06:01.986 --> 00:06:03.905
He's so bright and carefree.

00:06:04.530 --> 00:06:08.326
Looking at him is like looking at a clear blue sky without a single cloud.

00:06:10.495 --> 00:06:12.288
Yet he also has a big heart.

00:06:13.081 --> 00:06:15.083
At first, I was simply fascinated.

00:06:16.084 --> 00:06:18.127
Wondering how he grew up to be like that.

00:06:19.295 --> 00:06:21.547
But it clicked after I visited his home.

00:06:24.008 --> 00:06:26.135
Why he was so different.

00:06:29.430 --> 00:06:30.431
It was his family.

00:06:32.975 --> 00:06:34.811
Thanks to his loving family

00:06:35.728 --> 00:06:38.689
And thanks to him, I think I'm starting to understand

00:06:40.358 --> 00:06:41.859
What makes a home

00:06:43.236 --> 00:06:44.779
And what family truly means.

00:06:47.407 --> 00:06:49.075
I'm learning a little every day.

00:06:54.664 --> 00:06:55.790
Oh my.

00:06:56.833 --> 00:06:58.334
Goodness, young man.

00:06:58.960 --> 00:07:02.046
You thought all that every time you visited our home?

00:07:07.718 --> 00:07:10.680
You know what, Kang? You're not alone anymore.

00:07:13.099 --> 00:07:14.600
Don't you understand?

00:07:15.101 --> 00:07:17.770
I'm saying you can come over whenever you want.

00:07:18.646 --> 00:07:20.606
Consider this place your home.

00:07:21.482 --> 00:07:23.734
You're practically family now.

00:07:27.738 --> 00:07:29.907
<i>I only realized after opening the door</i>

00:07:30.658 --> 00:07:33.327
<i>which door it was that I had truly wanted to open.</i>

00:07:36.664 --> 00:07:38.040
<i>The door to their hearts.</i>

00:07:38.749 --> 00:07:42.670
<i>Only then does the divide between the inside and out disappear.</i>

00:07:46.215 --> 00:07:49.719
<i>P.S. I owe all of this to you, Mr. Heo.</i>

00:07:50.219 --> 00:07:52.429
<i>None of this would have been possible</i>

00:07:52.430 --> 00:07:54.765
<i>if you hadn't slipped me the competition problems.</i>

00:07:55.641 --> 00:07:57.852
<i>Thank you, Mr. Heo.</i>

00:08:07.695 --> 00:08:11.115
What are you doing here? Why did you read this without my permission?

00:08:12.658 --> 00:08:15.453
What was that about competition problems?

00:08:16.412 --> 00:08:19.916
You slipped him the problems? What on earth did you do?

00:08:21.459 --> 00:08:22.793
What problems?

00:08:23.961 --> 00:08:25.338
What are you talking about?

00:08:25.838 --> 00:08:27.215
You don't know, do you?

00:08:27.757 --> 00:08:30.301
That you wrinkle your nose when you lie.

00:08:31.761 --> 00:08:34.263
Enough. I have a lot to do. Get out.

00:08:37.850 --> 00:08:40.520
Look. It's written right here at the end.

00:08:41.437 --> 00:08:42.980
- Let go. - Hand it here.

00:08:45.566 --> 00:08:46.566
Are you insane?

00:08:46.567 --> 00:08:49.778
So why lie? What did he mean about competition problems?

00:08:49.779 --> 00:08:51.113
Just drop it!

00:08:51.614 --> 00:08:52.740
What's it to you?

00:08:54.992 --> 00:08:56.202
"What's it to you?"

00:08:57.995 --> 00:08:59.204
Please.

00:08:59.205 --> 00:09:01.206
Just leave me alone.

00:09:01.207 --> 00:09:03.251
Stop trying to know everything.

00:09:04.126 --> 00:09:07.128
And from now on, don't come in here without permission.

00:09:07.129 --> 00:09:08.881
Or read my students' assignments.

00:09:10.967 --> 00:09:13.135
Just mind your own business!

00:09:19.684 --> 00:09:22.937
That damn lunatic. Why did he even write that?

00:09:38.411 --> 00:09:39.453
Oh my God!

00:09:42.999 --> 00:09:45.543
What are you doing? You startled me.

00:09:48.087 --> 00:09:49.422
I called your name.

00:09:50.256 --> 00:09:51.549
And knocked.

00:09:53.467 --> 00:09:54.302
What?

00:09:54.802 --> 00:09:55.886
Why are you here?

00:10:03.144 --> 00:10:04.604
What are you doing?

00:10:11.819 --> 00:10:14.238
I don't recall saying you could lie down.

00:10:22.622 --> 00:10:23.748
Yeah.

00:10:25.666 --> 00:10:27.585
I did something bad.

00:10:30.046 --> 00:10:31.422
Lee Kang, that punk.

00:10:32.423 --> 00:10:33.757
They were problems

00:10:33.758 --> 00:10:36.510
For his programming competition or whatever.

00:10:38.512 --> 00:10:40.181
I stole them and gave them to him.

00:10:43.726 --> 00:10:45.269
Don't ask any more questions.

00:10:46.354 --> 00:10:48.439
I just had to do it, so I did.

00:10:49.357 --> 00:10:51.067
What's that supposed to mean?

00:10:51.817 --> 00:10:52.735
But how...

00:10:53.444 --> 00:10:54.737
How could you...

00:10:57.823 --> 00:11:01.826
Whatever the reason, this isn't like you. Stealing competition problems?

00:11:01.827 --> 00:11:03.371
I know that too.

00:11:05.790 --> 00:11:07.625
It wasn't like me.

00:11:12.046 --> 00:11:13.214
But...

00:11:17.802 --> 00:11:18.928
It was thrilling.

00:11:20.221 --> 00:11:21.055
What?

00:11:23.015 --> 00:11:24.975
That's what made it even more thrilling.

00:11:26.602 --> 00:11:28.354
It was something I'd never do.

00:11:30.940 --> 00:11:32.608
I'd never felt like that before.

00:11:41.575 --> 00:11:42.785
<i>How should I put it?</i>

00:11:43.619 --> 00:11:48.165
<i>It felt like jumping over my own fence for the first time in my life.</i>

00:11:56.215 --> 00:11:59.093
Are you saying crossing the line made you feel liberated?

00:12:00.386 --> 00:12:01.971
Someone as bullheaded as you?

00:12:02.847 --> 00:12:04.181
Liberation? Please.

00:12:05.057 --> 00:12:06.976
That's just how it felt at the time.

00:12:10.229 --> 00:12:13.482
Come to think of it, you have been acting a little strange.

00:12:14.316 --> 00:12:15.735
Even now.

00:12:16.819 --> 00:12:18.654
You're lying here on my bed.

00:12:27.872 --> 00:12:29.290
You can sleep here.

00:12:34.462 --> 00:12:38.132
If you want to sleep here, you can. I don't mind.

00:13:00.696 --> 00:13:01.781
How long has it been...

00:13:04.617 --> 00:13:07.787
Since we started sleeping in separate rooms?

00:13:09.663 --> 00:13:11.207
How long?

00:13:12.958 --> 00:13:14.126
Twelve years?

00:13:15.044 --> 00:13:17.046
No, it's been 13 years.

00:13:20.549 --> 00:13:22.134
It was since then.

00:13:23.719 --> 00:13:25.471
When we gave up on IVF.

00:14:35.457 --> 00:14:37.625
Eat this with Lee Kang when he gets here.

00:14:37.626 --> 00:14:39.670
Today is your first real lesson, isn't it?

00:14:40.170 --> 00:14:41.422
Okay, thanks.

00:14:41.922 --> 00:14:43.549
You should head out now.

00:14:46.010 --> 00:14:49.555
No, I don't have anywhere to be today. I'll stay here with you.

00:14:51.432 --> 00:14:54.767
- You don't mean in this room, do you? - Is that a problem?

00:14:54.768 --> 00:14:57.813
Why would you be here for the lesson?

00:14:58.397 --> 00:15:01.692
Why are you getting so worked up? I was just kidding.

00:15:07.615 --> 00:15:09.366
Why are you getting all awkward?

00:15:09.992 --> 00:15:12.161
- You won't even look at me. - As if.

00:15:14.163 --> 00:15:16.206
You haven't changed a bit.

00:15:17.166 --> 00:15:18.833
Though I did always find it cute.

00:15:18.834 --> 00:15:22.086
Come on. Stop talking nonsense and get out.

00:15:22.087 --> 00:15:23.923
He'll be here any minute.

00:15:25.966 --> 00:15:27.551
Wait, I have a question.

00:15:28.719 --> 00:15:32.681
Did you know about what Lee Kang wrote in his assignment?

00:15:33.474 --> 00:15:35.059
About his personal life.

00:15:35.976 --> 00:15:38.562
I felt bad for him while reading that part.

00:15:39.271 --> 00:15:42.942
I didn't. He and I have never talked about that stuff before.

00:15:44.026 --> 00:15:46.028
Never? Not even once?

00:15:48.906 --> 00:15:50.740
That's the problem with you.

00:15:50.741 --> 00:15:54.369
You're a writer who teaches literature, yet you don't care about people.

00:15:54.370 --> 00:15:55.537
What could he learn?

00:15:57.623 --> 00:15:58.916
Here we go again!

00:16:01.710 --> 00:16:02.544
Please leave.

00:16:36.370 --> 00:16:37.830
What's with the flowers?

00:16:38.497 --> 00:16:42.543
Since today's lesson is in the morning, I figured your wife would be home.

00:16:43.043 --> 00:16:45.713
I couldn't show up empty-handed the first time we met.

00:16:46.213 --> 00:16:47.923
But they were expensive.

00:16:48.674 --> 00:16:50.009
I could only afford three.

00:16:51.885 --> 00:16:53.095
Are you kidding me?

00:16:54.388 --> 00:16:58.225
You wrote that in your assignment about the three white roses.

00:17:01.895 --> 00:17:03.188
Right, so I did.

00:17:04.314 --> 00:17:06.775
But it's true. Roses are expensive.

00:17:08.652 --> 00:17:09.653
Whatever.

00:17:11.613 --> 00:17:12.573
Let me ask.

00:17:14.616 --> 00:17:17.286
What you wrote about your life in your assignment,

00:17:18.287 --> 00:17:19.121
Is it true?

00:17:26.628 --> 00:17:29.715
Are you asking if the narrator in my assignment and the author

00:17:30.257 --> 00:17:32.301
Are the same person?

00:17:33.552 --> 00:17:34.553
Then what?

00:17:35.929 --> 00:17:37.014
You made that up?

00:17:38.807 --> 00:17:41.226
Not exactly, but I don't know.

00:17:42.519 --> 00:17:44.855
They could be the same yet different, you know?

00:17:45.731 --> 00:17:48.776
Is the narrator in your novel the same person as the author?

00:17:50.819 --> 00:17:51.652
My novel?

00:17:51.653 --> 00:17:52.780
Yes.

00:17:53.489 --> 00:17:54.364
Your novel.

00:18:04.833 --> 00:18:05.709
TWELVE WOMEN

00:18:06.043 --> 00:18:09.129
I stumbled upon it at a secondhand bookstore.

00:18:10.047 --> 00:18:12.132
I haven't finished it yet,

00:18:12.925 --> 00:18:17.262
But it seems to be about a man who wanders between 12 different women.

00:18:17.763 --> 00:18:19.556
Let's stop talking about this book.

00:18:22.059 --> 00:18:23.102
This book is...

00:18:24.937 --> 00:18:26.772
Too complex for you to understand yet.

00:18:29.942 --> 00:18:32.027
Actually, no one can understand it.

00:18:32.528 --> 00:18:36.073
No. Although it's a bit complex, I'm finding it interesting.

00:18:39.451 --> 00:18:43.497
So is the narrator in this novel the same person as the author?

00:18:44.123 --> 00:18:44.957
Well?

00:18:47.918 --> 00:18:49.545
I'm dying to know.

00:19:01.682 --> 00:19:02.891
Yeah.

00:19:04.893 --> 00:19:06.228
Just as you said...

00:19:11.066 --> 00:19:14.027
The author and the narrator can indeed be identical,

00:19:15.320 --> 00:19:16.822
Or they can be different.

00:19:19.199 --> 00:19:20.909
The twelve women

00:19:22.286 --> 00:19:24.037
Were mere figments of my imagination.

00:19:31.503 --> 00:19:33.714
The truth is, it was about one woman.

00:19:35.966 --> 00:19:36.800
Sorry?

00:19:37.885 --> 00:19:38.718
What was that?

00:19:38.719 --> 00:19:39.928
Enough.

00:19:41.638 --> 00:19:43.599
Let's stop talking about narrators.

00:19:44.683 --> 00:19:46.727
Let's start the lesson. Put that away.

00:19:47.352 --> 00:19:50.105
- No, what did you just say? - Put it away, please.

00:19:56.195 --> 00:20:00.157
I actually have something to tell you before we start the lesson.

00:20:01.658 --> 00:20:02.784
Some good news.

00:20:04.161 --> 00:20:05.913
I'm moving

00:20:07.039 --> 00:20:08.457
Into Se-yun's house.

00:20:10.167 --> 00:20:11.084
Moving in?

00:20:18.926 --> 00:20:22.804
<i>It came up when we were eating after a game of basketball.</i>

00:20:23.305 --> 00:20:25.432
- Move in? - Yeah, move in.

00:20:27.309 --> 00:20:30.436
Ever since I heard about you living in that budget micro-unit.

00:20:30.437 --> 00:20:31.688
It's been on my mind.

00:20:35.234 --> 00:20:37.778
Sorry, I told him about your place.

00:20:39.655 --> 00:20:42.950
You wouldn't be a burden, so just come live with us, okay?

00:20:43.450 --> 00:20:46.828
His sister just happens to be moving out, so we have a spare room.

00:20:47.371 --> 00:20:50.207
And Yun's mom is also on board, of course.

00:20:52.334 --> 00:20:55.503
As adults, it's our duty and reward

00:20:55.504 --> 00:20:58.048
To support smart kids like you.

00:20:59.216 --> 00:21:01.551
So don't worry about it. Just move in, okay?

00:21:02.469 --> 00:21:03.345
Eat up.

00:21:04.513 --> 00:21:07.349
Consider it your home and come live with us.

00:21:12.980 --> 00:21:13.855
And

00:21:15.440 --> 00:21:16.315
You agreed?

00:21:16.316 --> 00:21:17.609
Of course.

00:21:18.110 --> 00:21:20.070
Saving on rent is a huge deal for me.

00:21:21.113 --> 00:21:23.322
And it'd be good for our lessons too.

00:21:23.323 --> 00:21:25.784
I could write about what I see and feel every day.

00:21:27.244 --> 00:21:32.748
Still, letting someone into their home can't be an easy thing for them.

00:21:32.749 --> 00:21:37.296
You think I don't know that? That's what makes Mr. Kim so amazing.

00:21:38.255 --> 00:21:40.173
Se-yun told me later

00:21:40.757 --> 00:21:43.510
That his mom only agreed because his dad was so adamant.

00:21:44.845 --> 00:21:48.307
Se-yun says he respects his dad more than anyone else in the world.

00:21:49.224 --> 00:21:50.892
He's strong yet considerate

00:21:51.810 --> 00:21:53.812
And has a young, flexible mindset.

00:21:55.063 --> 00:21:57.274
Mr. Kim is a really admirable guy.

00:21:59.693 --> 00:22:01.528
I think he's the first adult I've met...

00:22:04.031 --> 00:22:05.282
That I want to be like.

00:22:11.663 --> 00:22:14.750
You've got a long way to go if you want to be a writer.

00:22:15.250 --> 00:22:16.083
Sorry?

00:22:16.084 --> 00:22:19.420
You're too hasty to make up your mind about people.

00:22:19.421 --> 00:22:21.340
And your judgment is shallow and simple.

00:22:21.840 --> 00:22:24.884
You think he's great, amazing, and you want to be like him

00:22:24.885 --> 00:22:27.095
Just because of that one thing?

00:22:31.224 --> 00:22:32.309
All right, fine.

00:22:32.976 --> 00:22:35.394
You're still young, so I guess it's understandable.

00:22:35.395 --> 00:22:36.646
But...

00:22:40.025 --> 00:22:41.735
You should know this.

00:22:43.195 --> 00:22:48.283
So far, you've only seen that man and his family at a surface level.

00:22:48.784 --> 00:22:51.745
A perfect middle-class family that lacks nothing.

00:22:52.245 --> 00:22:55.707
It's obvious and cliché. A textbook example.

00:22:57.209 --> 00:23:00.754
Do you know why that is? Because that's how you want to see them.

00:23:01.880 --> 00:23:03.673
That's what you want them to be.

00:23:07.803 --> 00:23:08.970
When it comes to people,

00:23:09.471 --> 00:23:11.223
What matters isn't who they are.

00:23:11.723 --> 00:23:14.768
It's their relationships. That's what you need to look out for.

00:23:15.268 --> 00:23:18.021
That's the only way to see their true selves.

00:23:20.649 --> 00:23:23.026
Since you've already decided to move in...

00:23:25.445 --> 00:23:26.738
For now...

00:23:28.990 --> 00:23:32.410
Start with Mr. Kim and study his various relationships.

00:23:32.411 --> 00:23:34.246
Observe them closely.

00:23:35.247 --> 00:23:36.832
This is your first assignment.

00:23:37.457 --> 00:23:38.583
Okay.

00:23:43.547 --> 00:23:44.381
Eat up.

00:23:47.300 --> 00:23:50.720
<i>Weren't you just envious of that dad?</i>

00:23:51.721 --> 00:23:53.140
What do you mean "envious"?

00:23:54.391 --> 00:23:55.308
Well,

00:23:55.809 --> 00:23:59.604
Because Lee Kang kept complimenting him,

00:24:00.147 --> 00:24:02.691
Saying he was the first adult he wanted to be like.

00:24:03.191 --> 00:24:04.901
Maybe you were just envious.

00:24:05.527 --> 00:24:06.695
Am I wrong?

00:24:07.446 --> 00:24:08.321
Hey, wait.

00:24:08.822 --> 00:24:12.451
What do you take me for? Do you think I'm that childish?

00:24:13.034 --> 00:24:15.911
If not, then fine. That's just what it sounded like to me.

00:24:15.912 --> 00:24:18.874
Were you eavesdropping again? How much did you hear?

00:24:19.374 --> 00:24:21.584
I didn't mean to listen in.

00:24:21.585 --> 00:24:23.837
I just caught bits here and there.

00:24:26.798 --> 00:24:29.717
I was just saying what needed to be said.

00:24:29.718 --> 00:24:34.181
He was being too one-sided, so I restored balance, as his teacher.

00:24:35.015 --> 00:24:36.016
That's true.

00:24:36.516 --> 00:24:39.643
To someone who's starved for attention, such kindness can feel huge.

00:24:39.644 --> 00:24:41.354
And it is a pretty big deal.

00:24:43.315 --> 00:24:45.025
You could try being nicer to him too.

00:24:45.525 --> 00:24:48.904
I know you want him to look up to you as an adult.

00:24:50.155 --> 00:24:53.365
That Lee Kang kid is actually pretty cute.

00:24:53.366 --> 00:24:55.076
He has a peculiar charm.

00:24:59.206 --> 00:25:01.458
But doesn't he look familiar?

00:25:03.543 --> 00:25:05.378
Earlier, when I first saw him...

00:25:07.214 --> 00:25:08.590
Hello, nice to meet you.

00:25:10.217 --> 00:25:12.511
Oh my, you shouldn't have.

00:25:13.178 --> 00:25:15.263
It's nice to meet you. Come on in.

00:25:22.312 --> 00:25:23.146
I don't know.

00:25:31.404 --> 00:25:34.658
So did Lee Kang say whether it was true or not?

00:25:35.158 --> 00:25:36.785
What he wrote in his assignment.

00:25:37.494 --> 00:25:39.621
Why are you so interested?

00:25:40.205 --> 00:25:41.455
Ever the therapist.

00:25:41.456 --> 00:25:43.083
I know, right?

00:25:43.667 --> 00:25:45.544
It keeps weighing on my mind.

00:25:46.461 --> 00:25:51.340
I wonder if his childhood was even harder than his writing implies,

00:25:51.341 --> 00:25:52.509
Given his deflection.

00:25:53.301 --> 00:25:55.470
Who knows what that kid is thinking?

00:25:56.888 --> 00:25:59.891
You don't think he'll do something strange at that house, do you?

00:26:02.769 --> 00:26:05.188
Never mind. It's just the therapist in me.

00:26:05.814 --> 00:26:06.898
Something strange?

00:26:07.482 --> 00:26:08.358
Like what?

00:26:09.693 --> 00:26:12.654
Well, you know how people are.

00:26:13.572 --> 00:26:15.155
They can only endure

00:26:15.156 --> 00:26:19.077
Because they have people who believe in them and support them.

00:26:19.578 --> 00:26:23.790
And their sense of ethics tends to be determined by those relationships.

00:26:24.499 --> 00:26:27.586
It seems like he hasn't had anyone like that in his life.

00:26:29.087 --> 00:26:31.172
I'm just concerned.

00:26:32.257 --> 00:26:35.468
Lonely people can become a dangerous presence

00:26:36.052 --> 00:26:38.430
When put in certain situations.

00:26:39.139 --> 00:26:40.348
It's sad.

00:26:44.603 --> 00:26:46.104
A dangerous presence?

00:26:47.105 --> 00:26:48.023
Yes.

00:26:49.441 --> 00:26:50.692
What are you doing?

00:26:51.484 --> 00:26:53.944
Mr. Heo, look here.

00:26:53.945 --> 00:26:57.157
I made this game. Want to take a look?

00:26:58.658 --> 00:27:02.495
You press down to move forward and double-click to do this.

00:28:00.762 --> 00:28:02.013
Some dream.

00:28:16.194 --> 00:28:18.488
Hello, I'm Lee Kang--

00:28:31.501 --> 00:28:34.129
There you are. Well done for making it here.

00:28:34.629 --> 00:28:35.547
Here. Let me.

00:28:36.047 --> 00:28:38.591
<i>The reason a trip is considered a trip...</i>

00:28:44.514 --> 00:28:46.349
<i>is because you have a home to return to.</i>

00:28:57.318 --> 00:28:58.736
But this is your sister's room.

00:28:58.737 --> 00:29:02.657
I told you she moved out. She only comes home a few times a year.

00:29:03.366 --> 00:29:04.325
It's your room now.

00:29:06.995 --> 00:29:07.829
All yours.

00:29:16.212 --> 00:29:19.257
Are you sure you'll be okay here? We don't even use this room.

00:29:20.049 --> 00:29:21.176
It's fine.

00:29:23.178 --> 00:29:25.597
We should clear some of the junk out.

00:29:26.389 --> 00:29:29.225
<i>And because you have your own room to return to.</i>

00:29:29.934 --> 00:29:32.478
I thought it'd upset her if her room was gone.

00:29:32.479 --> 00:29:35.857
It was an easy decision when I put myself in her shoes.

00:29:36.983 --> 00:29:38.692
Goodness, how sweet of you.

00:29:38.693 --> 00:29:40.778
And you're so considerate.

00:29:40.779 --> 00:29:42.655
You've never even met her.

00:29:43.448 --> 00:29:46.951
It's still a hundred times better than my old place. I couldn't be happier.

00:29:47.619 --> 00:29:49.412
All right, then. A welcome toast.

00:29:50.705 --> 00:29:51.623
Lee Kang,

00:29:52.207 --> 00:29:53.707
Welcome to the family.

00:29:53.708 --> 00:29:55.125
Welcome.

00:29:55.126 --> 00:29:56.419
Welcome!

00:29:59.172 --> 00:30:00.715
Speak of the devil.

00:30:01.216 --> 00:30:03.176
- It's Jeong-hu. - Of course it is.

00:30:05.178 --> 00:30:07.347
I'm so nice, I'm letting you keep your room.

00:30:08.056 --> 00:30:10.809
<i>Whatever. I told you I don't care.</i>

00:30:11.309 --> 00:30:14.394
<i>This is my room and my home now.</i>

00:30:14.395 --> 00:30:15.521
There you go again.

00:30:15.522 --> 00:30:18.816
You're going to make your dad cry. He'll start crying from heartbreak.

00:30:18.817 --> 00:30:21.152
That's right, kid. You're not family anymore.

00:30:21.778 --> 00:30:23.655
Just say hi. This is my friend.

00:30:24.405 --> 00:30:26.032
- <i>Lee Kang?</i> - Hello.

00:30:27.700 --> 00:30:31.496
<i>Hey. Yun's told me so much about you. I feel like we've already met.</i>

00:30:33.081 --> 00:30:34.791
<i>- See you around.</i> - Sure.

00:30:35.708 --> 00:30:38.001
- Don't skip any meals. - Bye.

00:30:38.002 --> 00:30:41.714
<i>It's because you have people who welcome you when you're back.</i>

00:30:42.215 --> 00:30:43.423
<i>Dad!</i>

00:30:43.424 --> 00:30:45.510
<i>Does that mean I can now</i>

00:30:46.135 --> 00:30:47.846
<i>go on a trip too?</i>

00:30:49.264 --> 00:30:52.559
<i>Can I finally set off on a trip of my own?</i>

00:31:11.578 --> 00:31:13.495
What are you looking at, jerk?

00:31:13.496 --> 00:31:15.832
Thanks to you, I now have more work to do.

00:31:24.674 --> 00:31:27.093
<i>The one person who's ruining the thrill of a new trip.</i>

00:31:31.264 --> 00:31:33.558
I heard you lived in a budget micro-unit<i>.</i>

00:31:34.851 --> 00:31:36.227
Guess you struck gold.

00:31:45.361 --> 00:31:46.612
<i>Her name is Seon Min-hui.</i>

00:31:46.613 --> 00:31:48.655
<i>She's in her early-thirties, maybe?</i>

00:31:48.656 --> 00:31:50.867
<i>She comes to work three times a week.</i>

00:31:59.292 --> 00:32:00.710
Oh my gosh! Oh dear.

00:32:01.753 --> 00:32:02.878
Sorry.

00:32:02.879 --> 00:32:04.671
You should be more careful.

00:32:04.672 --> 00:32:06.174
It's okay. I'll do it.

00:32:12.680 --> 00:32:16.224
<i>She's the only person who hates that I moved into this house.</i>

00:32:16.225 --> 00:32:20.396
You can't throw your cigarette butts in the flower bed. This is yours, right?

00:32:21.314 --> 00:32:22.565
It isn't.

00:32:23.274 --> 00:32:24.608
It's not mine, it's his.

00:32:24.609 --> 00:32:26.986
You know, that friend of Se-yun's. Lee Kang.

00:32:27.528 --> 00:32:28.488
I saw him do it.

00:32:28.988 --> 00:32:32.449
What are you talking about? Now you're even telling lies?

00:32:32.450 --> 00:32:35.411
Here, there's clearly lipstick on it.

00:32:36.120 --> 00:32:38.122
Besides, our kids don't smoke.

00:32:39.415 --> 00:32:42.961
As smoking is a preference, I can't do anything about it, but still.

00:32:43.628 --> 00:32:46.005
I don't want anyone smoking in my home.

00:32:46.506 --> 00:32:48.091
It's bad for the flowers too.

00:32:49.425 --> 00:32:51.010
Please don't, okay?

00:32:59.686 --> 00:33:00.520
What?

00:33:01.312 --> 00:33:02.939
Bad for the flowers, you say?

00:33:42.979 --> 00:33:45.022
<i>Just hire someone else.</i>

00:33:45.023 --> 00:33:46.899
Why are you putting up with her?

00:33:47.400 --> 00:33:49.485
I can tell her for you if you find it hard.

00:33:49.986 --> 00:33:51.112
Oh, I don't know.

00:33:52.447 --> 00:33:54.490
I don't know what to do with her.

00:33:54.991 --> 00:33:57.535
I felt bad for her because she's a single mother.

00:33:58.453 --> 00:34:00.705
But if I fire her,

00:34:01.205 --> 00:34:04.041
I couldn't face the president of our church's volunteer group.

00:34:04.042 --> 00:34:05.752
They introduced her to me.

00:34:06.669 --> 00:34:10.923
You're overthinking things so much, it's making you cranky.

00:34:11.924 --> 00:34:12.800
Legs here.

00:34:17.263 --> 00:34:18.598
Still,

00:34:20.099 --> 00:34:21.893
She might be a bit unruly,

00:34:22.518 --> 00:34:24.896
But her side dishes are incredible.

00:34:25.646 --> 00:34:28.733
Our Yun devours all the side dishes Min-hui makes.

00:34:29.650 --> 00:34:30.651
That's good.

00:34:31.152 --> 00:34:34.071
That feels so good. That's the spot.

00:34:34.072 --> 00:34:34.989
Here?

00:34:35.656 --> 00:34:36.783
I'm good at this, right?

00:34:37.366 --> 00:34:38.451
You sure are.

00:34:39.077 --> 00:34:40.953
You get better by the day.

00:34:42.246 --> 00:34:43.873
You're as good as any masseuse.

00:34:50.171 --> 00:34:51.339
So,

00:34:52.006 --> 00:34:53.673
Please don't think too much.

00:34:53.674 --> 00:34:56.094
Don't let useless thoughts clutter your mind, okay?

00:34:57.595 --> 00:35:01.307
The most important thing to me is that you feel at peace, okay?

00:35:02.141 --> 00:35:03.226
In our family,

00:35:04.393 --> 00:35:06.562
Nothing matters more than that.

00:35:07.605 --> 00:35:09.898
Oh, all right.

00:35:09.899 --> 00:35:12.193
I can't say anything to you without you worrying.

00:36:00.032 --> 00:36:01.701
You know the kids are home, right?

00:36:02.201 --> 00:36:03.703
So what if they are?

00:36:38.070 --> 00:36:38.905
You didn't...

00:36:41.616 --> 00:36:43.117
Listen in on that, did you?

00:36:44.202 --> 00:36:45.703
No, Se-yun called me

00:36:46.746 --> 00:36:48.289
Not long after that.

00:36:54.003 --> 00:36:56.088
Why do you look so disappointed?

00:36:56.631 --> 00:36:57.465
Sorry?

00:37:01.510 --> 00:37:02.345
Hey.

00:37:02.845 --> 00:37:03.971
Don't.

00:37:05.139 --> 00:37:07.266
That's voyeurism, you know.

00:37:08.517 --> 00:37:11.604
I told you to be an observer, not a voyeur.

00:37:12.647 --> 00:37:13.856
That's unacceptable.

00:37:15.233 --> 00:37:16.358
What's the difference?

00:37:16.359 --> 00:37:17.777
The difference, you punk...

00:37:19.779 --> 00:37:20.738
Hold on.

00:37:30.498 --> 00:37:31.791
What are you doing?

00:37:39.757 --> 00:37:42.300
Deliberately spying on and eavesdropping on people.

00:37:42.301 --> 00:37:46.472
Anyway, the moment you start indulging in it, it becomes voyeurism.

00:37:47.598 --> 00:37:49.517
I didn't see them on purpose.

00:37:50.393 --> 00:37:51.727
It just happened.

00:37:53.187 --> 00:37:54.563
You sly bastard.

00:37:55.898 --> 00:37:57.733
Do you honestly think that's believable?

00:37:59.944 --> 00:38:02.238
Absolutely not. Observation only.

00:38:03.864 --> 00:38:07.325
Anyway, Mr. Kim really loves his wife.

00:38:07.326 --> 00:38:08.952
That's my point.

00:38:08.953 --> 00:38:11.038
From what I've observed,

00:38:12.623 --> 00:38:15.334
The two of them frequently share small touches.

00:38:15.835 --> 00:38:19.629
Do you think two people being touchy-feely always means it's love?

00:38:19.630 --> 00:38:21.631
If it's not love, what is it?

00:38:21.632 --> 00:38:26.178
Okay, yeah. You're still young, so you might see that as love.

00:38:26.679 --> 00:38:29.932
But you see, with married couples...

00:38:34.020 --> 00:38:37.148
It could very well be a desperate attempt

00:38:38.357 --> 00:38:40.526
To overcome the cold tedium

00:38:42.111 --> 00:38:43.528
That has settled over time.

00:38:43.529 --> 00:38:46.032
What am I even saying right now?

00:38:48.284 --> 00:38:51.579
Anyway, married couples are complicated, okay?

00:38:52.079 --> 00:38:53.664
Are you talking about yourself?

00:38:55.416 --> 00:38:56.250
What?

00:38:57.418 --> 00:39:00.880
Well, I'm just wondering how things are with you and your wife.

00:39:02.048 --> 00:39:04.508
Why are you curious about that?

00:39:06.302 --> 00:39:07.261
You little punk.

00:39:07.762 --> 00:39:10.473
You stepped on the line. Don't cross it.

00:39:14.143 --> 00:39:17.979
Hey, tell me more about that housekeeper.

00:39:17.980 --> 00:39:19.565
No, I don't want to.

00:39:20.483 --> 00:39:22.108
I don't want to talk about her.

00:39:22.109 --> 00:39:23.444
Why not?

00:39:24.737 --> 00:39:26.155
Does she keep harassing you?

00:39:27.490 --> 00:39:29.533
Tell me about you instead. Please?

00:39:31.660 --> 00:39:32.578
Do the two of you...

00:39:34.830 --> 00:39:35.998
Love each other?

00:39:36.540 --> 00:39:40.210
How do we seem to you? Do we look like we're in love?

00:39:40.211 --> 00:39:42.670
Why would you ask something like that?

00:39:42.671 --> 00:39:45.424
You're talking nonsense and to a little kid at that.

00:39:45.925 --> 00:39:48.677
What do you mean "a little kid"? He's an adult now.

00:39:49.178 --> 00:39:52.348
And he's at the age where he'd be curious about these things, right?

00:39:53.516 --> 00:39:56.811
It seems like you love Mr. Heo,

00:39:58.270 --> 00:39:59.980
But I'm not sure about Mr. Heo.

00:40:02.900 --> 00:40:06.529
You're right. I always wonder about him too.

00:40:07.446 --> 00:40:08.906
You tell me. Do you love me?

00:40:11.742 --> 00:40:12.742
Hey.

00:40:12.743 --> 00:40:14.578
Stop eating. Put that down.

00:40:16.038 --> 00:40:18.790
What are you doing? Our lesson ended ages ago.

00:40:18.791 --> 00:40:19.707
Hurry on home.

00:40:19.708 --> 00:40:23.504
What's your deal? I ordered this specifically for Kang.

00:40:24.004 --> 00:40:25.381
Take your time and eat up.

00:40:26.132 --> 00:40:27.550
You should have some too.

00:40:29.135 --> 00:40:30.135
You too, Mr. Heo.

00:40:30.136 --> 00:40:31.345
I am.

00:40:34.265 --> 00:40:37.852
Then maybe I'll try a piece too.

00:40:40.020 --> 00:40:42.314
No, I need to lose weight.

00:40:42.815 --> 00:40:44.442
You're trying to lose weight?

00:40:45.109 --> 00:40:47.236
But you're already so beautiful.

00:40:47.736 --> 00:40:48.988
Oh my, is that right?

00:40:52.366 --> 00:40:55.744
Thank you. You're the only one who compliments me like that.

00:40:58.247 --> 00:40:59.957
What a load of crap.

00:41:05.713 --> 00:41:09.633
The truth is, I think Mr. Heo loves you too.

00:41:10.134 --> 00:41:12.886
Maybe his love is so deep that it's invisible.

00:41:12.887 --> 00:41:14.013
You think so?

00:41:14.763 --> 00:41:16.307
What makes you think that?

00:41:17.683 --> 00:41:19.727
I finished reading Mr. Heo's book.

00:41:21.645 --> 00:41:25.733
After reading it, I realized who the one woman is.

00:41:27.902 --> 00:41:28.903
The one woman?

00:41:29.612 --> 00:41:31.655
Mr. Heo told me in a previous lesson

00:41:32.156 --> 00:41:36.576
That the 12 women are just symbolic, and it's actually about one woman.

00:41:36.577 --> 00:41:37.786
When did I say that?

00:41:38.746 --> 00:41:39.663
When did I say that?

00:41:40.164 --> 00:41:41.457
You said that.

00:41:42.082 --> 00:41:44.543
You said it quietly, but I definitely heard you.

00:41:45.044 --> 00:41:46.295
I'm guessing that one woman

00:41:47.546 --> 00:41:49.757
Is Ms. Jo, of course.

00:41:51.091 --> 00:41:51.926
Right?

00:41:56.263 --> 00:41:57.389
One woman?

00:42:12.279 --> 00:42:16.241
Hey, don't pay any mind to what that kid said as a joke.

00:42:16.242 --> 00:42:19.035
That kid was just spouting nonsense.

00:42:19.036 --> 00:42:20.287
Don't worry about it.

00:42:20.788 --> 00:42:22.414
Worry? Please.

00:42:22.998 --> 00:42:25.543
Your age-old first love? What a laugh.

00:42:27.962 --> 00:42:29.213
What? First love?

00:42:30.422 --> 00:42:31.756
It's that woman.

00:42:31.757 --> 00:42:35.636
The name that keeps coming up in your old draft notes.

00:42:36.262 --> 00:42:37.555
It must be her.

00:42:38.347 --> 00:42:40.724
That's all in the past. Ancient history.

00:42:41.350 --> 00:42:43.394
What does any of that matter now?

00:42:44.228 --> 00:42:46.146
Yeah, I didn't say anything about it.

00:42:47.648 --> 00:42:48.566
Still,

00:42:49.441 --> 00:42:52.736
I didn't know all 12 women were her.

00:42:53.487 --> 00:42:58.200
Then again, what do I even know about you?

00:43:09.003 --> 00:43:09.962
Lee Kang.

00:43:10.462 --> 00:43:12.339
That little smart-ass, I swear...

00:43:16.885 --> 00:43:19.888
<i>It doesn't always take a typhoon to sway a tree.</i>

00:43:24.101 --> 00:43:26.145
<i>Some trees can be uprooted</i>

00:43:26.645 --> 00:43:28.731
<i>with a mere passing breeze.</i>

00:43:29.982 --> 00:43:32.817
Why do you keep suspecting me?

00:43:32.818 --> 00:43:35.570
I told you, I didn't steal it!

00:43:35.571 --> 00:43:38.573
Why are you lying to me again when I found it right here?

00:43:38.574 --> 00:43:40.993
Then how else would it have ended up in here?

00:43:41.493 --> 00:43:43.412
How should I know?

00:43:44.121 --> 00:43:45.164
And also,

00:43:45.998 --> 00:43:48.334
Why would you go through my bag without permission?

00:43:49.668 --> 00:43:51.795
I'm sorry about that.

00:43:52.296 --> 00:43:54.380
But do you really think I wanted to look?

00:43:54.381 --> 00:43:56.716
I searched everywhere. I was at my wits' end!

00:43:56.717 --> 00:43:59.595
Why is it pouring all of a sudden?

00:44:02.931 --> 00:44:06.935
So what if your damn scarf is designer?

00:44:08.979 --> 00:44:12.524
If you keep doubting me like this,

00:44:13.317 --> 00:44:15.277
I won't be able to work here anymore.

00:44:16.737 --> 00:44:17.571
I quit.

00:44:25.579 --> 00:44:27.247
What's the matter this time?

00:44:27.748 --> 00:44:28.707
Well,

00:44:29.208 --> 00:44:30.876
Min-hui stole my new scarf...

00:44:31.794 --> 00:44:33.545
Mom!

00:44:34.672 --> 00:44:35.589
Are you okay?

00:44:36.090 --> 00:44:38.800
- Should I bring you your sedatives? - Yeah, get me my meds.

00:44:38.801 --> 00:44:40.052
Yeah, okay.

00:44:43.722 --> 00:44:47.810
This is why I told you not to stress and just hire someone else!

00:44:49.687 --> 00:44:50.854
Damn it.

00:44:52.147 --> 00:44:54.190
That's it. I'll have a firm word with her.

00:44:54.191 --> 00:44:55.484
Honey...

00:45:00.948 --> 00:45:02.324
Are you out of your mind?

00:45:06.203 --> 00:45:10.207
You've gone beyond being a voyeur and are actually messing with them now?

00:45:12.042 --> 00:45:12.960
You're telling me

00:45:14.461 --> 00:45:16.505
You snuck the scarf in her bag?

00:45:18.966 --> 00:45:20.300
I did,

00:45:20.801 --> 00:45:22.593
But she messed with me first.

00:45:22.594 --> 00:45:25.596
She spilled drinks on me on purpose and kept belittling me.

00:45:25.597 --> 00:45:27.641
You think this is on the same level?

00:45:28.600 --> 00:45:29.435
So, what?

00:45:30.144 --> 00:45:31.812
You wanted to get her fired?

00:45:32.688 --> 00:45:34.856
No, I was just pulling a prank--

00:45:34.857 --> 00:45:37.484
A prank? What do you mean "prank"?

00:45:38.944 --> 00:45:40.154
What you did

00:45:40.988 --> 00:45:42.990
Was frame someone as a thief.

00:45:43.907 --> 00:45:44.950
You crossed a line.

00:45:48.912 --> 00:45:50.748
I wouldn't have done that

00:45:51.373 --> 00:45:53.083
If she hadn't messed with me.

00:45:58.881 --> 00:46:00.382
You punk, you really...

00:46:00.883 --> 00:46:03.802
You go around causing trouble with every family you visit!

00:46:06.263 --> 00:46:07.264
Every family?

00:46:11.935 --> 00:46:13.687
Look, kid, what I mean is...

00:46:14.605 --> 00:46:16.690
I told you over and over again, didn't I?

00:46:17.274 --> 00:46:22.820
I told you to observe relationships, not to go around sparking conflict.

00:46:22.821 --> 00:46:23.906
Right?

00:46:24.656 --> 00:46:26.700
Meddling and starting arguments.

00:46:27.659 --> 00:46:29.328
A writer shouldn't do that.

00:46:31.997 --> 00:46:35.918
After our last lesson, did you argue with your wife because of what I...

00:46:38.462 --> 00:46:40.296
Is that why we're here today for--

00:46:40.297 --> 00:46:44.092
Argue? We didn't argue! Don't act like you know everything!

00:46:48.096 --> 00:46:49.014
Anyway,

00:46:49.890 --> 00:46:52.392
Our lessons will take place here from now on. Period.

00:46:53.477 --> 00:46:54.311
Yes, sir.

00:46:57.439 --> 00:46:59.149
Man, I'm exhausted.

00:47:00.067 --> 00:47:02.611
Let's call it a day. We'll continue next time.

00:47:07.866 --> 00:47:08.992
But, Mr. Heo,

00:47:09.701 --> 00:47:11.077
I learned a shocking truth.

00:47:11.078 --> 00:47:14.039
I was going to write it, but I wanted to tell you in person.

00:47:17.167 --> 00:47:19.086
You were right, Mr. Heo.

00:47:20.420 --> 00:47:22.798
You can't judge a person by what you see.

00:47:23.674 --> 00:47:24.675
Keep it short.

00:47:25.551 --> 00:47:28.178
There's something going on between Mr. Kim and Min-hui.

00:47:32.057 --> 00:47:32.891
That day...

00:47:34.518 --> 00:47:36.186
I saw them that day.

00:47:43.068 --> 00:47:47.364
<i>Mr. Kim stepped outside, saying he'd have a firm word with Min-hui, but...</i>

00:48:08.886 --> 00:48:10.804
<i>they looked like a couple.</i>

00:48:13.807 --> 00:48:17.935
Then Se-yun's dad grabbed her, and they went into the garage.

00:48:17.936 --> 00:48:21.148
So I secretly followed them, and I saw... I saw...

00:48:43.462 --> 00:48:45.504
The car was shaking.

00:48:45.505 --> 00:48:47.882
Shaking like this. What else could that mean?

00:48:47.883 --> 00:48:48.967
Hey!

00:48:52.512 --> 00:48:54.014
Is this why you moved in?

00:48:54.514 --> 00:48:57.184
To spy on them and make assumptions?

00:48:57.684 --> 00:49:01.354
Do you think I'm giving you these lessons so I can listen to this bullshit?

00:49:01.355 --> 00:49:03.481
No, I really saw it!

00:49:03.482 --> 00:49:04.899
You saw it? Really?

00:49:04.900 --> 00:49:07.693
You said you felt dizzy that day. Are you sure you saw that?

00:49:07.694 --> 00:49:09.404
Yes, of course I saw...

00:49:15.661 --> 00:49:16.536
Lee Kang.

00:49:17.663 --> 00:49:19.206
What you're saying right now

00:49:19.748 --> 00:49:24.962
Is no different from indiscriminately swinging a hammer at people.

00:49:25.462 --> 00:49:26.963
Just like in that game you made.

00:49:26.964 --> 00:49:29.674
That unethical and irresponsible attitude of yours.

00:49:29.675 --> 00:49:32.302
Caring only for entertainment regardless of the truth!

00:49:35.722 --> 00:49:36.807
But the thing is...

00:49:38.850 --> 00:49:40.644
Literature is not a game.

00:49:42.646 --> 00:49:45.691
Your attitude must be sincere. That's of the utmost importance.

00:49:48.819 --> 00:49:50.529
In order to write a good story,

00:49:52.114 --> 00:49:53.949
You have to be a decent human being.

00:49:56.660 --> 00:49:57.494
Got it?

00:50:07.796 --> 00:50:09.589
I think you were right.

00:50:16.346 --> 00:50:17.556
Lee Kang, that punk.

00:50:19.391 --> 00:50:22.310
I think there's something off about that bastard.

00:50:23.186 --> 00:50:24.896
I think I need to stop the lessons.

00:50:29.317 --> 00:50:32.320
Isn't that why you liked him? Because he was stimulating?

00:50:33.155 --> 00:50:34.489
I quite like him.

00:50:35.907 --> 00:50:37.242
What the heck?

00:50:38.160 --> 00:50:40.245
You said he was dangerous and all that.

00:50:42.039 --> 00:50:43.707
That was your takeaway?

00:50:44.791 --> 00:50:46.459
Such poor comprehension skills.

00:50:46.460 --> 00:50:47.377
What?

00:50:48.295 --> 00:50:50.338
I was just briefly worried.

00:50:51.256 --> 00:50:52.924
But I'm not worried anymore.

00:50:53.800 --> 00:50:56.136
He seems more normal than you.

00:51:00.807 --> 00:51:02.851
What? Are you still...

00:51:04.227 --> 00:51:05.812
Am I still what?

00:51:06.354 --> 00:51:08.774
I have a lot of reports to write. Please leave.

00:51:53.568 --> 00:52:00.575
LEE KANG

00:52:12.838 --> 00:52:13.672
What is it?

00:52:14.172 --> 00:52:15.382
<i>Were you sleeping?</i>

00:52:15.882 --> 00:52:18.260
<i>I'm so sorry, but I got into an accident.</i>

00:52:18.844 --> 00:52:20.929
<i>I need a guardian, so could you...</i>

00:52:21.638 --> 00:52:23.390
<i>Could you please come here?</i>

00:52:23.890 --> 00:52:25.308
What? An accident?

00:52:25.809 --> 00:52:29.646
<i>You'll get the details when you're here. It's urgent, so please hurry.</i>

00:52:31.439 --> 00:52:32.524
But

00:52:33.150 --> 00:52:34.316
Why did you contact me?

00:52:34.317 --> 00:52:36.610
<i>You were the first person who came to mind.</i>

00:52:36.611 --> 00:52:38.321
<i>I could have called Mr. Kim,</i>

00:52:38.905 --> 00:52:41.992
<i>but still, I'd like for you to come.</i>

00:52:48.498 --> 00:52:50.625
Fine. Where are you?

00:53:19.529 --> 00:53:20.447
What's going on?

00:53:24.326 --> 00:53:25.911
What accident, exactly?

00:53:27.495 --> 00:53:28.496
I'm sorry.

00:53:29.581 --> 00:53:30.665
The truth is...

00:53:35.503 --> 00:53:36.545
Did you lie to me?

00:53:36.546 --> 00:53:38.297
I'll tell you everything.

00:53:38.298 --> 00:53:39.423
The truth is...

00:53:39.424 --> 00:53:40.425
Look over there.

00:53:40.926 --> 00:53:42.384
Just now,

00:53:42.385 --> 00:53:44.638
Mr. Kim and Min-hui went into that hotel.

00:53:45.138 --> 00:53:47.015
I saw them by chance and followed them.

00:53:51.770 --> 00:53:53.730
I wanted you to see it for yourself,

00:53:54.773 --> 00:53:56.274
Since you wouldn't believe me.

00:53:58.318 --> 00:53:59.236
Mr. Heo!

00:53:59.778 --> 00:54:01.987
I told you, I saw them! Why won't you believe me?

00:54:01.988 --> 00:54:03.782
Fine, you punk!

00:54:04.282 --> 00:54:06.493
Let's say you did see them. So what?

00:54:06.993 --> 00:54:10.247
What does such vulgar gossip have to do with me?

00:54:12.999 --> 00:54:15.877
You dragged me here for this crap, by lying, no less?

00:54:18.296 --> 00:54:19.380
I'm done with you.

00:54:19.381 --> 00:54:21.341
I can't waste any more of my time

00:54:21.841 --> 00:54:23.927
On this foolishness.

00:54:25.887 --> 00:54:28.932
I don't need this. Our lessons are over.

00:54:29.432 --> 00:54:30.558
Over!

00:54:34.813 --> 00:54:35.646
Oh my God!

00:54:35.647 --> 00:54:36.815
What the...

00:54:40.360 --> 00:54:42.570
Oh no, she's bleeding. Hurry!

00:55:06.553 --> 00:55:07.846
That's her.

00:55:10.307 --> 00:55:11.308
Min-hui.

00:55:12.767 --> 00:55:13.643
What did you say?

00:55:14.144 --> 00:55:15.520
An ambulance. Hurry!

00:55:23.528 --> 00:55:24.529
That's Mr. Kim.

00:55:25.030 --> 00:55:27.365
- She's bleeding. - Where?

00:55:41.046 --> 00:55:41.880
That...

00:55:42.630 --> 00:55:44.883
That man is...

00:55:47.093 --> 00:55:48.303
Mr. Kim?

00:55:49.387 --> 00:55:50.680
Se-yun's dad?

00:55:52.724 --> 00:55:53.558
Yes.

00:56:19.250 --> 00:56:20.168
That man...

00:56:22.128 --> 00:56:23.296
Is Mr. Kim?

00:56:48.863 --> 00:56:52.367
So you're Se-yun's new friend. Nice to meet you. Lee Kang, right?

00:57:15.056 --> 00:57:16.307
Kim Su-hun.

00:57:17.934 --> 00:57:19.310
Kim Su-hun...

00:57:25.191 --> 00:57:26.609
Is Se-yun's dad?

00:58:13.198 --> 00:58:16.201
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

01:00:42.305 --> 01:00:47.310
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi

